The paper discusses local search algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The investigation is carried out in the framework of parameterized complexity (cs.CC), which is a common approach to analyzing the computational complexity of combinatorial problems. The paper also discusses the Vertex Cover problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses a relaxation of strict local search, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) to improve the performance of optimization algorithms.
